03:34.463 --> 03:36.328
How you doing, Keaton?

03:39.769 --> 03:41.669
I can't feel my legs...

03:44.206 --> 03:45.605
Keyser.

03:49.779 --> 03:51.076
Ready?

04:02.725 --> 04:04.090
What time is it?

04:05.461 --> 04:06.621
12:30.

05:12.228 --> 05:15.163
It all started back in New York
six weeks ago.

05:15.297 --> 05:18.892
A truck loaded with stripped gun parts
got jacked outside of Queens.

05:18.968 --> 05:21.402
The driver didn't see anyone,
but someone fucked up.

05:21.470 --> 05:24.098
He heard a voice.
Sometimes that's all you need.

05:27.743 --> 05:32.180
- Mr. McManus?
- Christ! Don't you fucking guys ever sleep?

05:32.681 --> 05:35.479
- We have a warrant for your arrest.
- Fuck you, pig.

05:43.259 --> 05:44.726
Todd Hockney?

05:45.060 --> 05:48.325
- Who wants to know?
- New York Police Department.

05:52.902 --> 05:54.733
- Shit.
- Freeze!

05:54.804 --> 05:56.135
Hold it!

06:01.110 --> 06:02.907
Sure you brought enough guys?

06:38.681 --> 06:39.841
<i>It's quite simple, really.</i>

06:39.915 --> 06:44.784
A restaurant that changes with the taste
without losing the overall aesthetic.

06:44.854 --> 06:46.082
In other words...

06:46.155 --> 06:49.249
the atmosphere will not be painted 
on the walls.

06:51.227 --> 06:54.424
- Let me give you an example-
- This I had to see for myself.

06:57.066 --> 06:58.055
David.

06:59.435 --> 07:02.404
- I'm in a meeting.
- Time for another one.

07:02.571 --> 07:04.937
Everyone, this is David Kujan.

07:05.241 --> 07:08.039
Special Agent Kujan. US Customs.

07:08.377 --> 07:11.904
These gentlemen
are from the New York Police Department.

07:12.047 --> 07:14.948
You look good.
Better than I would have thought.

07:16.819 --> 07:19.913
A small matter of a stolen truck
loaded with guns.

07:22.591 --> 07:23.956
Mr. Keaton?

07:24.760 --> 07:26.591
Will you excuse us for a moment?

07:28.864 --> 07:32.595
We have some questions to ask you downtown. 
You'll be a while.

07:33.168 --> 07:35.636
No. Please, sit down.

07:36.105 --> 07:39.199
This is a small problem.

07:40.142 --> 07:43.339
Enjoy the meal. 
I'll talk to you later.

08:05.467 --> 08:07.731
<i>It didn't make sense that I'd be there.</i>

08:07.803 --> 08:10.533
<i>These guys were hard-core hijackers...</i>

08:10.773 --> 08:12.536
<i>but there I was.</i>

08:15.110 --> 08:17.135
<i>At that point, I wasn't scared.</i>

08:17.212 --> 08:20.147
<i>I knew I hadn't done anything
they could do me for.</i>

08:21.050 --> 08:22.813
<i>Besides, it was fun.</i>

08:23.319 --> 08:25.753
<i>I got to make like I was notorious.</i>

08:26.689 --> 08:28.247
<i>You all know the drill.</i>

08:28.324 --> 08:33.023
<i>When your number is called, step forward
and repeat the phrase you've been given.</i>

08:33.462 --> 08:35.429
<i>Number 1, step forward.</i>

08:39.969 --> 08:43.097
"Hand me the keys you fucking cocksucker."

08:44.840 --> 08:46.808
<i>Number 2, step forward.</i>

08:49.678 --> 08:53.307
Gimme the fuckin' keys,
you fuckin' cocksucker motherfucker!

08:53.382 --> 08:57.045
Knock it off. Get back.
Number 3, step forward.

09:06.028 --> 09:09.589
- "Hand me the keys, you cocksucker. "
<i>- In English, please.</i>

09:09.832 --> 09:12.699
- Excuse me?
<i>- In English.</i>

09:13.469 --> 09:16.438
Hand me the fuckin' keys, you cocksucker.
What the fuck?

09:16.505 --> 09:18.439
<i>Number 4, step forward.</i>

09:18.674 --> 09:21.472
<i>It was bullshit.
The whole rap was a setup.</i>

09:21.677 --> 09:24.737
"Hand me the keys you fucking cocksucker."

09:25.014 --> 09:26.572
<i>It was the cops' fault.</i>

09:26.649 --> 09:29.709
<i>You don't put guys like that
into a room together.</i>

09:29.885 --> 09:31.910
<i>Who knows what can happen?</i>

09:32.121 --> 09:35.454
"Hand me the keys you fucking cocksucker."

09:36.291 --> 09:39.658
<i>This has really got to be embarrassing
for you guys.</i>

09:39.795 --> 09:40.989
<i>They drilled us all night.</i>

09:41.063 --> 09:44.328
<i>Someone was mad about that truck hijacking 
and the cops had nothing.</i>

09:44.400 --> 09:47.665
<i>They were hoping somebody would slip up
and give them something.</i>

09:47.736 --> 09:50.671
<i>They knew we wouldn't fight,
they knew how to lean on us.</i>

09:50.739 --> 09:53.867
<i>They've been doing it forever.
Our rights went out the window.</i>

09:53.942 --> 09:55.842
<i>It was a violation. Disgraceful.</i>

09:55.911 --> 09:58.744
<i>They went after McManus first.
Topnotch entry man.</i>

09:58.847 --> 10:00.246
What truck?

10:00.616 --> 10:03.744
- The truck with the guns, fucko.
- "Fucko"?

10:06.889 --> 10:09.221
<i>He was a good guy. Crazy, though.</i>

10:09.291 --> 10:11.384
Wanna know what your pal Fenster told us?

10:11.460 --> 10:13.189
- Say who?
- McManus.

10:13.262 --> 10:14.991
He told us another story.

10:15.230 --> 10:18.791
Is that the one about
the hooker with the dysentery?

10:18.967 --> 10:22.061
<i>Fenster always worked with McManus.
He was a real tight-ass.</i>

10:22.137 --> 10:25.402
<i>But when it came to the job,
he was right on. A smart man.</i>

10:25.474 --> 10:28.170
- What are you saying?
- I said he'll flip you.

10:28.243 --> 10:31.212
- He'll what?
- Flip you. Flip you for real.

10:31.280 --> 10:33.646
- I'm shaking. Come on.
- Okay.

10:33.716 --> 10:36.742
- Answer my questions.
- Can you hear me in the back?

10:37.820 --> 10:38.844
Hello?

10:39.421 --> 10:41.048
I want my lawyer.

10:41.390 --> 10:43.950
I'm gonna have your fuckin' badge, 
cocksucker.

10:44.359 --> 10:46.850
<i>Todd Hockney: good with explosives.</i>

10:47.329 --> 10:50.924
<i>Without a doubt, the one guy
who didn't give a fuck about anybody.</i>

10:51.066 --> 10:53.557
You guys don't have a fuckin' leg 
to stand on.

10:53.635 --> 10:54.897
You think so, tough guy?

10:54.970 --> 10:57.495
I can put you in Queens
during the hijacking.

10:57.573 --> 10:58.767
Really?

10:59.041 --> 11:00.508
I live in Queens.

11:00.576 --> 11:02.976
Did you put that together yourself, Einstein?

11:03.045 --> 11:05.639
You got a team of monkeys
working full time on this?

11:05.714 --> 11:09.047
You know what happens
if you do another turn in the joint?

11:10.519 --> 11:13.113
I fuck your father in the shower,
and have a snack.

11:13.188 --> 11:16.521
- Are you gonna charge me, dickhead?
- I'll charge you when I'm ready.

11:16.592 --> 11:19.390
- With what?
- You know damn well, dead man.

11:19.461 --> 11:20.485
<i>But Keaton?</i>

11:20.562 --> 11:23.224
<i>Keaton was the real prize for them
for obvious reasons.</i>

11:23.365 --> 11:26.027
It was your mistake, not mine.

11:28.704 --> 11:30.797
Did you ever stop to ask me?

11:32.307 --> 11:36.368
I've been walking around
with the same face, the same name.

11:37.813 --> 11:39.246
I'm a businessman.

11:39.314 --> 11:41.475
What's that? The restaurant business?

11:41.550 --> 11:45.452
No. From now on you're in the
"getting fucked by us" business.

11:45.521 --> 11:47.955
I'm gonna make you famous, cocksucker.

11:48.023 --> 11:49.615
Like I said...

11:49.925 --> 11:52.018
it was your mistake...

11:52.194 --> 11:53.627
not mine.

11:54.096 --> 11:56.428
You charge me with this shit...

11:57.566 --> 11:59.363
and I'll beat it.

12:00.302 --> 12:01.326
Okay?

12:02.371 --> 12:05.135
Let's get back to the truck, asshole.

12:06.608 --> 12:09.668
Really, somebody's got to do something
about this shit.

12:09.745 --> 12:13.146
They put me in holding every five minutes.
So I did a little time.

12:13.215 --> 12:17.675
Does that mean I get railed every time
a truck finds it's way gone?

12:17.753 --> 12:19.015
Fuck 'em.

12:19.454 --> 12:21.354
Fenster, will you relax?

12:21.690 --> 12:25.888
- These guys don't have any probable cause.
- You fuckin' right. No PC.

12:25.961 --> 12:29.419
You're goddamn right.
You do some time, never let you go.

12:29.498 --> 12:31.989
They treat me like a criminal.

12:32.334 --> 12:35.030
- I'll end up a criminal.
- You are a criminal.

12:36.605 --> 12:39.073
Why'd you got to go and do that?

12:39.374 --> 12:42.901
- I'm trying to make a point.
- Why don't you make your point?

12:42.978 --> 12:45.173
You're making me tired all over.

12:45.314 --> 12:46.372
Fuck it then.

12:47.082 --> 12:49.243
- I heard you were dead.
- Yeah?

12:49.585 --> 12:52.554
- You heard right.
- Word I got is you hung up your spurs.

12:53.255 --> 12:56.088
- What's that all about?
- What's this?

12:56.391 --> 13:00.953
Rumor has it Keaton's gone straight.
I hear he's tapping Edie Finneran.

13:01.029 --> 13:02.053
Who's that?

13:02.264 --> 13:04.755
She's a heavyweight 
criminal lawyer from uptown.

13:04.833 --> 13:06.767
I hear she's Keaton's meal ticket.

13:06.969 --> 13:08.766
How 'bout it, Keaton?

13:08.971 --> 13:10.666
You a lawyer's wife?

13:11.406 --> 13:13.374
What kind of retainer you giving her?

13:17.045 --> 13:18.910
Do your friend a favor...

13:19.648 --> 13:21.377
tell him to keep quiet.

13:22.384 --> 13:23.874
Dean Keaton...

13:25.354 --> 13:26.946
Gone clean?

13:27.456 --> 13:29.048
Say it ain't so.

13:29.358 --> 13:32.657
- Or was it you that hit that truck?
- Mac, forget him.

13:32.995 --> 13:35.225
Did you get to talk to your lawyer?

13:35.964 --> 13:37.795
This whole thing was a shakedown.

13:38.100 --> 13:41.592
- What makes you say that?
- How many times you been in a lineup?

13:42.771 --> 13:44.932
It's always you and four dummies.

13:45.007 --> 13:48.272
The PD are paying homeless guys
$10 a head half the time.

13:48.543 --> 13:51.740
There's no way they'd line
five felons in the same row.

13:52.014 --> 13:55.677
- What's a voice lineup?
- Public defender could get you out of that.

13:55.751 --> 13:59.243
- Why the hell was I strip searched?
- It was the feds.

13:59.488 --> 14:01.820
A truckload of guns gets snagged.

14:01.890 --> 14:05.656
Customs comes down on NYPD for answers. 
They come up with us.

14:05.894 --> 14:09.022
- They're clutching at straws.
- I had a guy's finger up my ass.

14:09.197 --> 14:10.459
Is it Friday already?

14:12.601 --> 14:13.795
Yeah, lover boy.

14:13.936 --> 14:17.030
You want a piece? Jump in. 
I'll love you.

14:17.239 --> 14:20.902
So who in the goddamn piss hell
stole our fucking truck?

14:21.810 --> 14:24.870
- What did you say?
- Who stole the fucking truck?

14:24.947 --> 14:28.075
- I don't want to know.
- Who asked you, workingman?

14:28.150 --> 14:30.880
Fuck who did it.
What I want to know is, who's the gimp?

14:30.953 --> 14:33.217
- He's okay.
- Says you. How do I know that?

14:33.288 --> 14:35.381
What about it, pretzel man?
What's your story?

14:35.457 --> 14:36.754
His name is Verbal.

14:37.492 --> 14:38.823
Verbal Kint.

14:38.894 --> 14:40.384
- Verbal?
- Yeah.

14:40.462 --> 14:43.590
Roger, really. 
People say I talk too much.

14:43.832 --> 14:45.732
I was going to tell you to shut up.

14:45.901 --> 14:49.530
- We met before, once or twice.
- In County. I was in for fraud.

14:49.604 --> 14:51.868
You were in a lineup then, too.
What happened?

14:52.040 --> 14:54.873
I walked. 90 days, suspended.

14:55.177 --> 14:57.941
- So you did it.
- All right, now look...

14:59.314 --> 15:02.078
we've all been put out
by this whole thing, right?

15:02.250 --> 15:05.981
I figure we owe it to ourselves
to salvage a little dignity.

15:06.488 --> 15:09.753
Now, me and Fenster
heard about a little job.

15:09.891 --> 15:11.688
Why don't you just calm down?

15:12.160 --> 15:14.094
What do you care what he has to say?

15:15.163 --> 15:17.028
I'm just talking here.

15:17.499 --> 15:20.525
It seems to me like Mr. Hockney
wants to hear it...

15:20.602 --> 15:22.593
and I know Fenster's down.

15:23.438 --> 15:25.201
What about you, guy?

15:26.575 --> 15:27.940
I'm interested.

15:29.211 --> 15:30.405
There. See?

15:30.779 --> 15:33.805
I'd like to exercise my right
to free assembly.

15:34.049 --> 15:35.846
Why don't you just shut up?

15:41.923 --> 15:43.481
You're missing the point.

15:44.159 --> 15:45.217
No.

15:46.328 --> 15:48.296
You're missing the point.

15:48.497 --> 15:50.931
I don't want to hear anything from you.

15:51.500 --> 15:53.491
I don't care about your job.

15:55.337 --> 15:56.463
And...

15:58.640 --> 16:01.165
I want nothing to do with any of you.

16:01.643 --> 16:04.840
I beg your pardon,
but you can all go to hell.

16:07.516 --> 16:08.813
Dean Keaton...

16:09.584 --> 16:11.074
gone the high road.

16:12.621 --> 16:14.714
What is the world coming to?

16:19.728 --> 16:20.990
Fuck him.

16:25.700 --> 16:27.361
<i>And that was how it started:</i>

16:27.436 --> 16:29.836
<i>The five of us brought in
on a trumped-up charge...</i>

16:29.905 --> 16:31.873
<i>to be leaned on by half-wits.</i>

16:35.177 --> 16:37.645
I really can't talk about it much here.

16:37.712 --> 16:41.307
<i>What the cops never figured out,
and what I know now...</i>

16:41.383 --> 16:44.648
<i>was that these men would never break,
never lie down.</i>

16:45.554 --> 16:47.647
<i>Never bend over for anybody.</i>

16:48.657 --> 16:49.885
<i>Anybody.</i>

17:05.840 --> 17:09.038
- Who are you?
- Agent Jack Baer, FBI.

17:09.310 --> 17:11.369
- How many dead?
- 15 so far.

17:11.445 --> 17:14.243
They're still pulling bodies
out of the water.

17:14.382 --> 17:16.349
- Any survivors?
- Two.

17:16.417 --> 17:19.215
One guy's in County hospital,
but he's in a coma.

17:19.287 --> 17:22.381
The DA has a second guy,
a cripple from New York.

17:22.457 --> 17:24.823
The chief wants this place sealed off.

17:24.925 --> 17:27.759
If you have any questions, give him a call.

18:01.863 --> 18:05.162
<i>This is Dave Kujan.
I'll be in Los Angeles until Tuesday.</i>

18:05.267 --> 18:09.465
<i>If you need to reach me, contact Jeff Rabin
of the San Pedro Police Department...</i>

18:09.538 --> 18:12.371
<i>at extension 112. Have a nice day.</i>

18:16.545 --> 18:18.706
<i>- Why can't I see him?
- I told you...</i>

18:18.780 --> 18:21.772
the DA came down here last night 
ready to arraign...

18:21.850 --> 18:23.909
even before they moved him to County.

18:23.985 --> 18:26.351
Kint's lawyer shows up five minutes later...

18:26.421 --> 18:29.948
the DA comes out looking like
the bogeyman smacked him around.

18:30.025 --> 18:33.153
They take his statement,
and they cut him a deal.

18:33.228 --> 18:37.255
- Did they charge him with anything?
- Weapons, misdemeanor 2.

18:37.632 --> 18:39.099
What is that?

18:39.668 --> 18:43.263
I give the DA credit for getting that much,
you understand?

18:43.338 --> 18:44.862
Excuse me, sir.

18:46.074 --> 18:50.033
This whole thing has turned political.
The mayor was here last night.

18:50.111 --> 18:53.444
The chief. 
This morning, the governor called, okay?

18:53.515 --> 18:57.713
I'm telling you, this guy is protected
from up on high by the Prince of Darkness.

18:57.786 --> 19:00.220
- Take my word for it.
- When does he post bail?

19:00.288 --> 19:02.518
- Maybe two hours, tops.
- I want to see him.

19:02.591 --> 19:04.456
- No.
- I gotta see him.

19:04.526 --> 19:07.188
- No. I can't-
- You gotta do this for me.

19:07.262 --> 19:09.492
I came a long way for this.

19:10.165 --> 19:11.632
Dave, please.

19:15.136 --> 19:18.003
Even if I let you talk to him,
he won't talk to you.

19:19.474 --> 19:21.305
He's paranoid about being recorded.

19:21.376 --> 19:23.970
- He knows the rooms are wired.
- I quit.

19:24.045 --> 19:27.014
This won't be an interrogation,
just a friendly chat.

19:27.215 --> 19:30.309
- He won't go into the interrogation room.
- Then someplace else.

19:30.385 --> 19:31.545
Where?

19:33.588 --> 19:34.816
No, no.

19:35.123 --> 19:38.752
If this was a dope deal, where's the dope?
If it was a hit, who called it?

19:38.827 --> 19:42.319
I'm sure you have a host of wild theories
to answer all these questions.

19:42.397 --> 19:45.764
- You know what I think.
- That's crazy, and it doesn't even matter.

19:45.834 --> 19:48.701
The guy's got total immunity.
His story checks out.

19:49.004 --> 19:53.236
- He doesn't know what you want to know.
- I don't think he does, not exactly.

19:53.575 --> 19:56.237
But there's a lot more to his story,
believe me.

19:56.611 --> 20:00.240
I wanna know why 27 men died on that pier...

20:00.315 --> 20:04.615
for what looks to be $91 million
worth of dope that wasn't there.

20:04.853 --> 20:08.289
And above all,
I want to be sure Dean Keaton's dead.

20:08.790 --> 20:10.052
He's dead.

20:10.458 --> 20:13.484
Come on. Two hours.
Just till he makes bail.

20:13.862 --> 20:15.295
They're all dead.

20:15.363 --> 20:17.661
I don't care how tough
you say Keaton was...

20:17.732 --> 20:20.633
nobody on that boat
could've come out alive.

20:23.872 --> 20:26.864
- Is he talking?
- He regained consciousness an hour ago.

20:26.941 --> 20:29.375
He spoke, not English, then he lapsed.

20:29.544 --> 20:31.944
- Hungarian?
- That might have been it.

20:32.013 --> 20:34.914
- Most of them were Hungarians.
- You gotta put this on.

20:34.983 --> 20:37.645
Burn victims are very susceptible to infection.

20:38.186 --> 20:40.654
And, of course, there's no smoking.

20:50.365 --> 20:52.993
Keep your mask up.
Please don't touch him.

20:53.068 --> 20:54.194
Is he gonna die?

20:54.302 --> 20:56.930
He's burned 60 percent of his body,
broken ribs-

20:57.005 --> 20:59.667
Call security. Put a man on the door.

20:59.741 --> 21:01.902
- Is he dangerous?
- Yes.

21:02.210 --> 21:03.302
Do it.

21:03.878 --> 21:05.243
Do it now!

21:08.350 --> 21:10.750
Joel? Baer. Down at LA County.

21:10.919 --> 21:14.878
Look, the guy they pulled out of the harbor
is Arkosh Kovash.

21:15.023 --> 21:16.786
Yes, I'm sure.

21:17.292 --> 21:18.987
No, he's all fucked up.

21:20.829 --> 21:22.456
I can't hear you.

21:23.098 --> 21:25.157
Will you shut up? I'm on the phone.

21:25.767 --> 21:26.791
Yes.

21:27.736 --> 21:29.670
No, not till I put a man on him.

21:29.804 --> 21:32.170
Send me someone who can speak Hungarian.

21:32.307 --> 21:35.037
He's awake.
He's talking like a Thai hooker.

21:35.110 --> 21:36.475
Keyser Soze.

21:37.712 --> 21:40.010
- What?
- Keyser Soze!

21:44.919 --> 21:46.147
No shit?

21:47.622 --> 21:50.420
Call Dan Metzheiser over at Justice...

21:50.759 --> 21:53.023
and find Dave Kujan from Customs.

22:27.061 --> 22:30.360
Verbal, this is Agent Kujan from Customs.

22:31.166 --> 22:32.633
Nice to meet you.

22:32.767 --> 22:35.292
He wants to ask you a few questions
before you go.

22:35.370 --> 22:38.828
- What about?
- About a Dean Keaton, mostly.

22:40.074 --> 22:42.542
I'd like to start at the lineup
back in New York.

22:42.610 --> 22:45.943
- Can I get some coffee?
- In a while. Let's talk about the lineup.

22:46.114 --> 22:49.413
I'm really thirsty.
I used to dehydrate as a kid.

22:49.484 --> 22:51.850
Once I got so bad
my piss come out like snot.

22:51.920 --> 22:54.946
- It was all thick and gooey-
- I'll get your fucking coffee.

22:55.023 --> 22:57.583
Get me one, too, while you're at it.

23:01.996 --> 23:03.691
That guy is tense.

23:03.932 --> 23:05.593
Tension is a killer.

23:05.700 --> 23:08.669
I used to be in a barbershop quartet
in Skokie, Illinois.

23:08.736 --> 23:11.671
The baritone was this guy
named Kip Diskin, big fat guy.

23:11.773 --> 23:14.401
Like, orca fat.
