Redfoot, Dean Keaton.

43:56.283 --> 44:00.276
- Todd Hockney and Verbal Kint.
- Verbal, the man with the plan.

44:01.121 --> 44:02.645
You interested in more work?

44:03.557 --> 44:06.492
- We're always looking for extra work.
- We're on vacation.

44:08.061 --> 44:09.494
That's too bad.

44:09.863 --> 44:12.058
I got a ton of work and no good people.

44:12.499 --> 44:14.433
- Not like you guys.
- What's the job?

44:14.835 --> 44:17.565
There's this jeweler
out of Texas named Saul.

44:17.637 --> 44:19.730
He rents a suite in some downtown hotel.

44:20.040 --> 44:23.441
He does free appraisals.
Sometimes he buys, sometimes he doesn't.

44:23.777 --> 44:26.302
The word is,
he carries around a lot of cash.

44:27.114 --> 44:31.107
So I figure, I keep the merchandise,
you keep the green.

44:31.585 --> 44:33.917
- Simple.
- What about security?

44:33.987 --> 44:37.320
A couple of bodyguards.
Nothing you couldn't handle.

44:37.524 --> 44:39.355
Give me time to check it out?

44:39.726 --> 44:41.887
I expect nothing less from you, man.

44:43.230 --> 44:45.289
Good to see you. We'll call you.

44:45.365 --> 44:47.765
Enjoy LA. Get yourself laid.

44:53.173 --> 44:57.166
A friend in New York tells me
that you knew Spook Hollis.

44:58.145 --> 45:01.205
The way I hear it,
you did time with ol' Spook.

45:01.348 --> 45:03.145
A good man, wasn't he?

45:03.550 --> 45:05.575
I used to run dope for him.

45:06.219 --> 45:08.312
Too bad he got shivved.

45:10.357 --> 45:11.517
I shivved him.

45:14.094 --> 45:17.621
Better you hear it from me now
than from somebody else later.

45:19.099 --> 45:20.760
I appreciate that.

45:21.768 --> 45:23.633
But just out of curiosity...

45:24.204 --> 45:26.866
was it business or personal?

45:29.309 --> 45:30.799
A bit of both.

45:32.345 --> 45:34.006
Like I said...

45:34.381 --> 45:37.248
you give me a call if you're interested.

45:41.388 --> 45:43.117
Is there a problem?

45:44.825 --> 45:46.019
One job.

45:46.526 --> 45:48.153
That was the deal.

45:53.433 --> 45:54.661
One job?

45:57.704 --> 45:58.932
One job?

46:00.640 --> 46:02.574
That's a good one.

46:04.845 --> 46:08.337
<i>Keaton fought it as best he could,
but a man can't change what he is.</i>

46:08.515 --> 46:11.609
<i>He can convince anyone he's someone else,
but never himself.</i>

46:11.685 --> 46:15.314
<i>It took one day with McManus nagging,
and we went back to work.</i>

46:30.036 --> 46:32.596
I get out of my car,
and the thing is wrecked.

46:32.672 --> 46:36.164
I look in the backseat of the other car,
and this woman's totally naked.

46:36.243 --> 46:39.337
- I'm laughin' so hard I can't breathe.
- Get in the car, Saul.

46:39.546 --> 46:42.208
- Freeze, motherfucker!
- Stay right there!

46:44.150 --> 46:46.084
There's a second one here, somewhere.

46:49.823 --> 46:53.054
Gimme the case. 
Give me the fuckin' case!

46:59.232 --> 47:02.668
Give me the fuckin' case.
I'm tellin' you for the last time.

47:02.903 --> 47:04.666
Give me the fuckin' case!

47:09.142 --> 47:11.667
- Come on!
- Don't move!

47:47.113 --> 47:48.740
Hand over the case.

47:49.883 --> 47:51.908
Hand over the fuckin' case.

48:15.909 --> 48:17.570
Come on, let's go!

48:18.211 --> 48:20.771
- Come on!
- Bad day. Fuck it.

48:21.514 --> 48:23.004
Let's go!

48:47.240 --> 48:48.332
Fuck.

48:51.478 --> 48:55.175
- Looks like a lot of china to me.
- Shit.

49:00.487 --> 49:01.977
Guys, come on.

49:03.289 --> 49:05.780
- What are you doin'?
- I'm gonna kill him.

49:05.859 --> 49:07.986
We did it your way, now we'll do it mine.

49:08.061 --> 49:10.222
- You gonna kill him?
- I'll deal with him.

49:10.296 --> 49:13.163
- You'd better, or I'm gonna.
- Shut up.

49:20.540 --> 49:22.974
What am I supposed to do with that?

49:23.276 --> 49:26.404
Feed it to the gimp. Ease his pain.
I don't know what that is.

49:26.479 --> 49:28.504
- What do you mean?
- I don't know.

49:28.748 --> 49:30.875
I got thrown this job by some lawyer.

49:30.950 --> 49:31.939
Who?

49:32.185 --> 49:34.210
I don't know. Some limey.

49:34.387 --> 49:38.016
He's a middleman for somebody.
He doesn't say, I don't ask.

49:38.091 --> 49:40.389
- You're fuckin' full of shit!
- Fuck you.

49:40.460 --> 49:42.155
- Fuck you.
- Listen to me.

49:42.562 --> 49:44.553
We wanna meet him, okay?

49:44.898 --> 49:46.365
That's funny.

49:47.133 --> 49:50.728
He called me last night.
He says he wants to meet you guys.

49:51.404 --> 49:53.304
Okay, we'll meet him.

49:53.706 --> 49:55.606
- I'll call you.
- Good. Let's go.

49:55.675 --> 49:59.042
I don't like it. Wait a minute.
One more thing, tough guy:

49:59.579 --> 50:02.309
Any more surprises, and I'm gonna kill you.

50:03.716 --> 50:06.742
You're such a tough guy.
But do me a favor, all right?

50:06.820 --> 50:08.981
Get the fuck off my dick.

50:09.422 --> 50:10.821
No!

50:11.925 --> 50:13.756
Put a leash on that puppy.

50:15.862 --> 50:19.127
It's an awful shame
about Saul gettin' whacked.

50:19.799 --> 50:21.960
Cops'll be lookin' for the guys who did it.

50:23.036 --> 50:25.664
Sooner or later,
they're gonna come around askin' me.

50:28.108 --> 50:30.338
You have a sweet night, ladies.

50:34.147 --> 50:35.409
Fuck you.

50:41.788 --> 50:44.689
- So this lawyer-
- Kobayashi.

50:45.425 --> 50:47.757
- Came from Redfoot.
- Right.

50:48.161 --> 50:50.994
And why leave this out
when you talked to the DA?

50:51.097 --> 50:53.065
Dave, someone to see you.

50:58.471 --> 51:00.564
I've been looking all over for you.

51:00.640 --> 51:04.269
You still after that coke that took a walk
out of that bloodbath yesterday?

51:04.344 --> 51:07.142
You can stop looking. 
There was no coke.

51:07.213 --> 51:10.876
I've been in LA County talking to a guy 
they pulled out of a drainpipe...

51:10.950 --> 51:12.713
yesterday after the shootout.

51:12.785 --> 51:14.980
He came to this morning,
he started talking.

51:15.054 --> 51:18.319
He's part of a Hungarian mob.
They dealt with gwats from Argentina.

51:18.391 --> 51:20.951
He says it was definitely not a dope deal.

51:21.027 --> 51:24.326
- But there were-
- We know. But he says no on the dope.

51:24.397 --> 51:27.924
This Hungarian tells me they were
pulling stumps for Turkey the next day.

51:28.001 --> 51:31.596
They had no time for that kind of product,
and no means to move it.

51:31.671 --> 51:33.662
- What's the money for?
- He didn't know.

51:34.007 --> 51:36.999
No one doing the deal knew
except for a few key people.

51:37.076 --> 51:39.374
They were all very hush about it, he says.

51:39.546 --> 51:43.778
- Whatever it was, it was very sensitive.
- I don't get it.

51:43.850 --> 51:46.114
You got the cripple in there from New York?

51:46.186 --> 51:47.778
Did he mention Keyser Soze?

51:48.021 --> 51:49.386
Who?

51:49.923 --> 51:51.823
Just bear with me here.

51:53.259 --> 51:56.023
- Who's Keyser Soze?
- Fuck!

51:57.063 --> 52:00.260
We've been goin' over this
for an hour and a half.

52:00.700 --> 52:04.602
What we need to do is find Redfoot
and get the hell out of here now.

52:04.671 --> 52:06.639
What we need to do is think.

52:06.940 --> 52:08.305
Think back.

52:09.442 --> 52:12.206
Somebody with power...

52:12.745 --> 52:15.908
somebody capable of tracking us
from New York to LA.

52:15.982 --> 52:19.076
- What the hell are we doing here?
- We're waiting.

52:19.652 --> 52:23.520
- Sit down.
- No. I'm hot, and I'm fuckin' bored.

52:23.590 --> 52:25.387
Mr. Hockney, do stay.

52:26.125 --> 52:27.490
Mr. Keaton.

52:27.894 --> 52:30.192
Mr. Fenster I recognize from his mug shots...

52:30.263 --> 52:32.094
as well as Mr. McManus.

52:32.165 --> 52:37.159
I can only assume that you are Mr. Kint,
the gentleman who disposed of Saul Berg.

52:37.237 --> 52:40.934
My employer sends his gratitude,
a most unexpected benefit.

52:42.175 --> 52:43.836
I am Mr. Kobayashi.

52:44.043 --> 52:48.742
I have been asked by my employer
to bring a proposal to you gentlemen.

52:48.815 --> 52:51.909
- What do you want?
- My employer requires your services.

52:54.087 --> 52:57.614
One job, one day's work. 
Very dangerous.

52:57.824 --> 53:01.282
He does not expect all of you to live.
But those of you who do...

53:01.494 --> 53:05.487
will have $91 million to divide between you 
in any way you see fit.

53:05.565 --> 53:07.157
Who's your boss?

53:09.402 --> 53:11.029
I work for Keyser Soze.

53:22.382 --> 53:23.610
Who's Keyser Soze?

53:23.683 --> 53:26.083
Judging by the sudden change in mood...

53:26.219 --> 53:29.188
I feel sure the rest of your associates 
can tell you.

53:29.389 --> 53:32.256
I come with an offer
directly from Mr. Soze.

53:32.558 --> 53:36.255
- An order, actually.
- What do you mean, "an order"?

53:36.462 --> 53:41.422
In 1981, you participated in the hijacking
of a truck in Buffalo, New York.

53:42.035 --> 53:45.664
The cargo was raw steel,
steel which belonged to Mr. Soze...

53:45.738 --> 53:49.834
and which was destined for Pakistan
to be used in a nuclear reactor.

53:50.109 --> 53:53.203
A most profitable violation of UN Regulations.

53:53.279 --> 53:55.338
You had no way of knowing this...

53:55.415 --> 53:58.578
because the fellow shipping the steel
was working for Soze...

53:58.651 --> 54:00.209
without his knowledge.

54:00.553 --> 54:03.249
Earlier this year,
Mr. Fenster and Mr. McManus...

54:03.323 --> 54:07.089
hijacked a two-prop cargo flight
out of Newark airport.

54:07.160 --> 54:11.426
The plane was carrying gold and platinum wiring 
also set for Pakistan.

54:12.031 --> 54:15.523
Two months ago,
Mr. Hockney stole a truck...

54:15.601 --> 54:18.126
carrying gun parts through Queens.

54:18.204 --> 54:21.833
Gun parts which were set to be destroyed
by the state of New York.

54:22.041 --> 54:25.875
They were to be lost in a way station
and rerouted to Belfast.

54:25.945 --> 54:28.914
Again, Mr. Soze using pawns
who had no knowledge.

54:29.282 --> 54:31.443
Which brings us to Mr. Kint.

54:32.618 --> 54:35.178
Nine months ago, one of Mr. Soze's...

54:35.254 --> 54:39.816
less than intelligent couriers was taken
in a complicated confidence scam...

54:40.560 --> 54:41.993
by a cripple.

54:42.362 --> 54:44.660
He was relieved of $62,000.

54:45.498 --> 54:48.331
Now, it has taken us some time to find you.

54:48.801 --> 54:52.635
Our intention was to approach you
after your apprehension in New York.

54:52.839 --> 54:54.204
You set up the lineup.

54:54.273 --> 54:57.504
Yes. You were not to be released
until I had come to see you.

54:57.577 --> 55:00.410
It seems Mr. Keaton's attorney,
Miss Finneran...

55:00.780 --> 55:04.307
was a little too effective
in expediting his release.

55:04.384 --> 55:06.579
Holding the rest of you
became a moot point.

55:06.886 --> 55:09.582
- What about Redfoot?
- Mr. Redfoot knew nothing.

55:09.756 --> 55:12.384
Mr. Soze rarely works
with the same people for long...

55:12.458 --> 55:15.222
and they never know
who they're working for.

55:15.361 --> 55:18.262
One cannot be betrayed
if one has no people.

55:19.265 --> 55:21.290
So, why are you telling us?

55:21.701 --> 55:25.865
Because you have stolen from Mr. Soze,
Mr. Fenster.

55:26.105 --> 55:27.163
All of you.

55:27.240 --> 55:30.903
That you did not know it
is the only reason you're still alive.

55:31.511 --> 55:35.174
He feels you owe him.
You will repay your debt.

55:35.615 --> 55:39.449
Fuck the debt, and fuck you.
How do we know you work for Soze?

55:39.919 --> 55:42.479
I don't think that is very relevant.

55:42.655 --> 55:45.818
All five of you are responsible
for the murder of Saul Berg...

55:45.892 --> 55:47.257
and his bodyguards.

55:47.527 --> 55:50.087
Mr. Redfoot can testify to your involvement.

55:50.163 --> 55:52.097
We can see to it that he will.

55:52.165 --> 55:55.225
- What's your point?
- The offer is this, gentlemen:

55:55.535 --> 55:57.696
Mr. Soze's primary interest...

55:58.070 --> 55:59.469
is narcotics.

55:59.705 --> 56:02.333
He has been competing, shall we say...

56:02.408 --> 56:04.876
with a group of Argentineans
for several years.

56:05.077 --> 56:07.910
Competing with Mr. Soze has taken its toll.

56:08.714 --> 56:11.308
These Argentineans are negotiating the sale...

56:11.384 --> 56:15.252
of $91 million in cocaine
in three days time.

56:15.555 --> 56:18.422
Needless to say,
this purchase will revitalize...

56:18.491 --> 56:21.255
the diminishing strength of their organization.

56:22.061 --> 56:25.326
Mr. Soze would like you to stop the deal.

56:26.532 --> 56:29.262
If you choose,
you may wait until after the buy.

56:29.335 --> 56:31.929
Whatever money changes hands is yours.

56:32.805 --> 56:37.606
Mr. Soze would like you to get to the boat
and destroy the cocaine onboard.

56:38.311 --> 56:42.270
And then you will be free
of your obligations to Mr. Soze.

56:44.584 --> 56:48.213
Give me one good reason
why I shouldn't kill you right now.

56:50.189 --> 56:52.783
A gift from Mr. Soze.

56:55.995 --> 56:57.758
Good day, gentlemen.

58:06.599 --> 58:10.194
They got my whole life in here,
everything I've done since I was 18.

58:10.469 --> 58:12.528
They fuckin' know everything.

58:12.705 --> 58:15.469
Everybody I've ever worked with
or did time with.

58:29.956 --> 58:30.980
No.

58:33.225 --> 58:35.489
- This isn't right.
- I don't know.

58:35.561 --> 58:38.655
Who's that guy who used
to talk about Soze in New York?

58:40.333 --> 58:44.497
- Bricks Marlin.
- He did jobs for him, indirect stuff.

58:45.071 --> 58:48.837
He said he always made five times 
more money on it than the job was worth.

58:49.475 --> 58:51.170
This guy's a pipe dream.

58:51.243 --> 58:53.404
Kobayashi's using him for window dressing.

58:53.946 --> 58:55.573
I don't know. 
This is bad.

58:56.082 --> 58:59.813
It's bullshit. This guy could be LAPD.
It's a fuckin' setup.

59:00.820 --> 59:03.687
The way I hear it,
Soze's some kind of butcher.

59:04.056 --> 59:08.288
- A peerless, psycho, fucked-up butcher.
- There is no Keyser Soze!

59:11.097 --> 59:12.655
Who is Keyser Soze?

59:13.833 --> 59:17.701
He's supposed to be Turkish.
Some say his father was German.

59:17.770 --> 59:19.795
Nobody ever believed he was real.

59:20.072 --> 59:23.200
Nobody knew him or saw anybody
that ever worked directly for him.

59:23.309 --> 59:26.335
To hear Kobayashi tell it,
anybody could have worked for Soze.

59:26.445 --> 59:29.505
You never knew. 
That was his power.

59:30.316 --> 59:33.217
The greatest trick the Devil ever pulled...

59:33.753 --> 59:36.654
was convincing the world he didn't exist.

59:38.090 --> 59:40.786
One story the guys told me,
the story I believe...

59:40.860 --> 59:42.555
was from his days in Turkey.

59:42.628 --> 59:45.563
There was a gang of Hungarians
that wanted their own mob.

59:45.631 --> 59:49.032
They realized that to be in power,
you didn't need guns...

59:49.101 --> 59:50.659
or money or even numbers.

59:50.736 --> 59:54.194
You just needed the will to do 
what the other guy wouldn't.

59:54.573 --> 59:57.974
After a while they come into power,
and then they come after Soze.

59:58.044 --> 01:00:01.343
He was small-time then.
Just running dope, they say.

01:00:03.616 --> 01:00:05.015
They come to his home...

01:00:05.418 --> 01:00:08.012
<i>in the afternoon looking for his business.</i>

01:00:08.087 --> 01:00:12.353
<i>They find his wife and kids in the house,
and decide to wait for Soze.</i>

01:00:28.140 --> 01:00:32.406
<i>He comes home to find his wife raped
and children screaming.</i>

01:00:32.478 --> 01:00:35.879
<i>The Hungarians knew Soze was tough,
not to be trifled with.</i>

01:00:35.948 --> 01:00:37.677
They let him know they meant business.

01:00:38.784 --> 01:00:40.308
<i>No!</i>

01:00:43.155 --> 01:00:46.647
<i>They tell him they want his territory,
all his business.</i>

01:00:47.026 --> 01:00:50.587
Soze looks over the faces of his family.

01:00:52.465 --> 01:00:55.923
Then he showed these men of will 
what will really was.

01:01:15.454 --> 01:01:18.423
<i>He tells them he would
rather see his family dead...</i>

01:01:18.824 --> 01:01:21.156
<i>than live another day after this.</i>

01:01:22.628 --> 01:01:24.755
<i>He lets the last Hungarian go...</i>

01:01:24.997 --> 01:01:28.933
waits until his family is in the ground,
and goes after the rest of the mob.

01:01:29.368 --> 01:01:31.996
He kills their kids, he kills their wives...

01:01:32.104 --> 01:01:34.334
he kills their parents and their friends.

01:01:34.874 --> 01:01:37.104
<i>He burns down the houses they live in...</i>

01:01:38.210 --> 01:01:39.973
<i>and the stores they work in.</i>

01:01:40.479 --> 01:01:44.006
<i>He kills people that owe them money.
And like that...</i>

01:01:45.351 --> 01:01:47.148
he's gone, underground.

01:01:47.219 --> 01:01:49.813
Nobody's ever seen him since.
He becomes a myth.

01:01:49.889 --> 01:01:53.052
A spook story that criminals
tell their kids at night.

01:01:53.125 --> 01:01:56.219
"Rat on your pop,
and Keyser Soze will get you."

01:01:57.163 --> 01:01:59.154
No one ever really believes.

01:01:59.398 --> 01:02:01.423
Do you believe in him?

01:02:03.969 --> 01:02:05.698
Keaton always said:

01:02:05.905 --> 01:02:09.341
"I don't believe in God,
but I'm afraid of him."

01:02:11.310 --> 01:02:13.210
I believe in God.

01:02:13.579 --> 01:02:17.606
And the only thing that scares me
is Keyser Soze.

01:02:24.490 --> 01:02:26.515
You give any weight to this?

01:02:26.592 --> 01:02:29.060
I can introduce you 
to Dan Metzheiser from Justice.

01:02:29.128 --> 01:02:32.791
He's got a file on Soze in DC.
It's been a hobby of his for a while.

01:02:32.898 --> 01:02:36.299
A lot of guys equate him to that reporter
on <i>The Incredible Hulk.</i>

01:02:41.307 --> 01:02:42.740
You've heard of him?

01:02:42.808 --> 01:02:44.673
Where? On the street?

01:02:44.743 --> 01:02:47.473
A few times. 
You know, outside stuff.

01:02:47.746 --> 01:02:51.773
Someone working for a guy who worked for a guy 
who got money from Soze.

01:02:51.851 --> 01:02:53.443
Shit like that.

01:02:54.220 --> 01:02:56.518
It could be an old badge. 
A hex sign.

01:02:56.589 --> 01:02:59.683
Keep people from fucking with you
when a name meant something.

01:02:59.758 --> 01:03:01.692
- But you're here.
- Shit, yeah.

01:03:01.927 --> 01:03:06.523
This guy's trying to walk out of a hospital
because he's so afraid of Soze.

01:03:06.866 --> 01:03:08.925
I'll run it up the flagpole.

01:03:10.369 --> 01:03:12.894
I came clean. 
I told it like it happened.

01:03:12.972 --> 01:03:14.496
So what about how I got there?

01:03:14.573 --> 01:03:17.736
It's so full of holes, 
the DA would've told me to forget amnesty.

01:03:17.810 --> 01:03:20.040
You got what you wanted out of me.
Big deal.

01:03:20.112 --> 01:03:22.945
- That's why you never told the DA?
- You tell me.

01:03:23.115 --> 01:03:26.380
If I told you the Loch Ness monster hired me, 
what would you say?

01:03:26.452 --> 01:03:28.716
Turn state's evidence.
We'll put you on the stand.

01:03:28.787 --> 01:03:31.278
I've got immunity.
What can you possibly offer me?

01:03:31.390 --> 01:03:34.985
If there really is a Keyser Soze,
he's gonna come lookin' for you.

01:03:35.461 --> 01:03:36.792
Where's your head?

01:03:37.296 --> 01:03:39.127
Where do you think the pressure is?

01:03:39.198 --> 01:03:42.395
Keyser Soze, or whatever you call him,
knows where I am right now.

01:03:42.601 --> 01:03:46.628
He has the burner on your ass to let me go
so he can scoop me up 10 minutes later.

01:03:46.939 --> 01:03:48.964
Immunity was just a deal with you assholes.

01:03:49.041 --> 01:03:50.941
I got a new problem when I post bail.

01:03:51.010 --> 01:03:53.501
Why play into his hands?
We can protect you.

01:03:54.546 --> 01:03:57.845
Thanks, Dave. Bang-up job so far.
Extortion, coercion.

01:03:57.917 --> 01:04:00.044
