01:34:32.883 --> 01:34:35.511
- Keaton was Keyser Soze.
- No.

01:34:35.586 --> 01:34:39.147
<i>A man who could wrangle the wills of men 
like Hockney and McManus.</i>

01:34:39.223 --> 01:34:41.748
<i>A man who could engineer a police lineup...</i>

01:34:41.825 --> 01:34:44.589
<i>through all his years of contacts in NYPD.</i>

01:34:44.661 --> 01:34:47.186
The kind of man
who could've killed Edie Finneran.

01:34:52.202 --> 01:34:55.035
She was found yesterday
at a hotel in Pennsylvania...

01:34:55.105 --> 01:34:56.970
shot twice in the head.

01:35:01.879 --> 01:35:04.712
What do you think about Keaton now?

01:35:06.016 --> 01:35:07.005
Edie?

01:35:07.084 --> 01:35:09.314
He used all of you to get him on that boat.

01:35:09.386 --> 01:35:12.787
<i>He couldn't get on alone.
He had to pull the trigger himself...</i>

01:35:12.856 --> 01:35:14.756
to make sure he got his man...

01:35:14.858 --> 01:35:16.917
the one man that could identify him.

01:35:18.028 --> 01:35:19.655
This is all bullshit.

01:35:19.897 --> 01:35:21.865
You said you saw him die.

01:35:24.268 --> 01:35:25.292
<i>Or did you?</i>

01:35:25.469 --> 01:35:27.835
You had to hide
when you heard the police cars.

01:35:27.905 --> 01:35:30.305
<i>You said you heard the shot
before the fire...</i>

01:35:30.774 --> 01:35:32.799
but you didn't see him die.

01:35:33.076 --> 01:35:35.874
- I knew him. He would never-
- He programmed you.

01:35:35.946 --> 01:35:38.574
<i>He programmed you to tell us
what he wanted you to.</i>

01:35:38.649 --> 01:35:40.879
<i>He knew we were close.
You said it yourself.</i>

01:35:40.951 --> 01:35:43.977
<i>Where was the political pressure
to protect you from?</i>

01:35:44.254 --> 01:35:45.278
It was Keaton.

01:35:45.355 --> 01:35:48.688
- Immunity was your reward.
- But why me?

01:35:49.259 --> 01:35:51.352
Why not Fenster or McManus or Hockney?

01:35:51.428 --> 01:35:54.124
Why me? I'm stupid.
I'm a cripple. Why me?

01:35:54.198 --> 01:35:55.631
Because you're a cripple.

01:35:56.166 --> 01:35:57.861
Because you're stupid.

01:35:58.135 --> 01:36:00.069
Because you're weaker than them.

01:36:04.374 --> 01:36:05.671
If he's dead...

01:36:06.109 --> 01:36:10.011
If what you say is true,
then it won't matter.

01:36:11.548 --> 01:36:14.415
It was his idea to hit the taxi service,
wasn't it?

01:36:14.518 --> 01:36:17.681
- Come on, tell me the truth.
- It was all Keaton.

01:36:18.989 --> 01:36:21.514
We followed him from the beginning.

01:36:23.293 --> 01:36:24.453
I didn't know.

01:36:24.962 --> 01:36:26.691
I saw him die.

01:36:27.531 --> 01:36:30.523
I believe he's dead. 
Christ.

01:36:31.768 --> 01:36:33.565
You're not safe on your own.

01:36:37.674 --> 01:36:38.902
You think he's...

01:36:39.209 --> 01:36:40.801
Keyser Soze?

01:36:41.578 --> 01:36:43.205
I don't know.

01:36:44.715 --> 01:36:48.674
Keyser Soze's a shield,
or like you said, a spook story.

01:36:49.753 --> 01:36:53.382
But I know Keaton, and someone
is out there pulling strings for you.

01:36:54.157 --> 01:36:57.593
- Stay here and let us protect you.
- I'm not bait. I post today.

01:36:57.861 --> 01:36:59.294
You posted 20 minutes ago.

01:36:59.863 --> 01:37:01.922
Capt. Leo wants you out of here.

01:37:02.199 --> 01:37:05.168
- Unless you turn state's.
- I'll take my chances.

01:37:05.502 --> 01:37:09.199
If someone wants to get you,
they're gonna get you out there.

01:37:09.273 --> 01:37:12.674
Turn state's evidence.
You might never see trial.

01:37:12.743 --> 01:37:13.937
Maybe so.

01:37:15.512 --> 01:37:17.412
But I'm not a rat.

01:37:34.197 --> 01:37:35.755
Fuckin' cops.

01:38:00.223 --> 01:38:02.817
Can I use your fax machine?

01:38:06.797 --> 01:38:09.493
You'll have to sign for these, Mr. Kint.

01:38:11.635 --> 01:38:13.227
One watch, gold.

01:38:13.737 --> 01:38:15.830
One cigarette lighter, gold.

01:38:16.707 --> 01:38:18.698
One pack of cigarettes. 
Thank you.

01:38:19.309 --> 01:38:21.334
We still got nothing.

01:38:21.645 --> 01:38:23.909
I know what I wanted to know about Keaton.

01:38:23.981 --> 01:38:25.608
Which is nothing.

01:38:26.116 --> 01:38:29.677
No matter.
He'll have to know how close we came.

01:38:30.187 --> 01:38:32.781
<i>Keyser Soze or no Keyser Soze...</i>

01:38:33.156 --> 01:38:36.091
<i>if Keaton is alive,
he's not comin' up again.</i>

01:38:36.526 --> 01:38:38.323
<i>I'll find him.</i>

01:38:38.795 --> 01:38:40.285
<i>Waste of time.</i>

01:38:43.100 --> 01:38:45.432
<i>A rumor's not a rumor that doesn't die.</i>

01:38:45.902 --> 01:38:47.028
<i>What?</i>

01:38:48.138 --> 01:38:49.105
<i>Nothing.</i>

01:38:51.141 --> 01:38:52.972
Man, you're a slob.

01:38:53.043 --> 01:38:55.375
But it all has a system.

01:38:56.246 --> 01:39:00.683
It all makes sense if you look at it right.
You gotta stand back from it.

01:39:01.985 --> 01:39:05.079
You wanna see a real horror show?
See my garage.

01:39:42.426 --> 01:39:44.485
<i>Convince me. Tell me every last...</i>

01:39:44.561 --> 01:39:47.553
<i>When I was in that barbershop quartet
in Skokie, Illinois...</i>

01:39:47.631 --> 01:39:51.192
<i>- Where's your head?
- We need to think, think back.</i>

01:39:51.268 --> 01:39:52.895
<i>I'm sure you've heard tall tales.</i>

01:39:52.969 --> 01:39:54.527
<i>- Bricks Marlin.
- This isn't right.</i>

01:39:54.638 --> 01:39:57.038
<i>- I just wanna hear your story.
- It's all there.</i>

01:39:57.107 --> 01:40:00.565
<i>- I'm tellin' it straight.
- Some guy in California called Redfoot.</i>

01:40:00.644 --> 01:40:03.135
<i>- A gift from Mr. Soze.
- Talk to me.</i>

01:40:03.213 --> 01:40:06.273
<i>- What about Redfoot?
- Mr. Redfoot knew nothing.</i>

01:40:06.349 --> 01:40:09.318
<i>- Using pawns...
- A big fat guy. Like, orca fat.</i>

01:40:09.386 --> 01:40:11.115
<i>There was a lawyer...</i>

01:40:11.488 --> 01:40:12.887
<i>Kobayashi...</i>

01:40:13.323 --> 01:40:16.451
<i>When I was picking beans in Guatemala 
we made fresh coffee.</i>

01:40:16.593 --> 01:40:19.528
<i>- I know you thought he was a good man.
- I know he was good.</i>

01:40:21.932 --> 01:40:24.833
<i>- You tell me every last detail.
- The strangest thing.</i>

01:40:24.901 --> 01:40:26.835
<i>How do you shoot the Devil in the back?</i>

01:40:26.903 --> 01:40:30.134
<i>This guy is protected 
from up on high by the Prince of...</i>

01:40:30.240 --> 01:40:32.538
<i>What's your story, pretzel man?</i>

01:40:32.609 --> 01:40:34.440
<i>- There was a lawyer.
- What lawyer?</i>

01:40:34.511 --> 01:40:35.671
<i>I am Mr. Kobayashi.</i>

01:40:35.745 --> 01:40:39.272
<i>- Kobayashi. Kobayashi.
- Tell me every last detail.</i>

01:40:39.349 --> 01:40:42.580
<i>- I work for Keyser Soze.
- Convince me. Convince me.</i>

01:40:57.868 --> 01:41:00.496
<i>Every creep and scumbag
that works the street...</i>

01:41:00.570 --> 01:41:02.663
<i>will know the name of Verbal Kint.</i>

01:41:03.306 --> 01:41:04.796
The cripple, did you see him?

01:41:04.875 --> 01:41:07.969
- The cripple! Which way did he go?
- He went out that way.

01:41:08.044 --> 01:41:10.638
<i>I know you know something.
I know you're not telling...</i>

01:41:10.714 --> 01:41:11.874
<i>I'm smarter than you...</i>

01:41:11.948 --> 01:41:14.439
<i>and I'm gonna find out
whether you like it or not.</i>

01:41:14.518 --> 01:41:16.418
<i>To a cop, the explanation
is never complicated.</i>

01:41:16.486 --> 01:41:18.078
<i>- It's always simple.
- The truth!</i>

01:41:18.155 --> 01:41:21.090
<i>There's no arch-criminal behind it all.</i>

01:41:21.158 --> 01:41:23.991
<i>Somebody with power,
somebody who is capable...</i>

01:41:24.194 --> 01:41:25.786
<i>Keyser Soze!</i>

01:41:26.563 --> 01:41:29.828
<i>You think a guy like that
gets this close to getting caught...</i>

01:41:29.966 --> 01:41:31.934
<i>and sticks his head out?</i>

01:41:32.836 --> 01:41:35.862
<i>Because you're stupid.
Because you're a cripple.</i>

01:41:35.939 --> 01:41:38.100
<i>What I wanna know is, who's the gimp?</i>

01:41:38.175 --> 01:41:40.507
<i>You've known the whole fuckin' time!</i>

01:41:40.577 --> 01:41:44.206
<i>If he comes up for anything it'll be for me. 
I'm sure Keaton is dead.</i>

01:41:44.281 --> 01:41:47.273
<i>I can't feel my legs, Keyser.</i>

01:41:47.450 --> 01:41:49.850
<i>First thing I learned on the job.
You know what?</i>

01:41:49.986 --> 01:41:53.444
<i>- How to spot a murderer.
- You got the cripple in there?</i>

01:41:53.523 --> 01:41:56.287
<i>- Did he mention Keyser Soze?
- Who?</i>

01:41:56.526 --> 01:41:58.050
<i>After that...</i>

01:41:58.528 --> 01:42:01.554
<i>my guess is you'll never hear 
from him again.</i>

01:42:22.085 --> 01:42:24.383
<i>The greatest trick the Devil ever pulled...</i>

01:42:24.554 --> 01:42:27.284
<i>was convincing the world he didn't exist.</i>

01:42:29.159 --> 01:42:30.319
<i>And like that...</i>

01:42:32.028 --> 01:42:33.359
<i>he's gone.</i>

